overview: The user initiated a request to enhance the aesthetic appeal of their
  sleep questionnaire application, which previously had a generic, template-like
  appearance. The approach involved a multi-phase redesign. Initially, a new
  sleep-themed color palette was introduced, followed by a complete overhaul of
  the main form layout, including decorative background elements, a redesigned
  progress indicator, and a subtle star pattern on card headers. All core UI
  components like checkboxes, radio buttons, sliders, and cards received
  polished styling with improved interactive states. Subsequently, all
  questionnaire sections were updated to ensure consistent theming, replacing
  old gray boxes with refined card-style groupings and theme-based colors.
  During this process, a console error related to  values being passed to
  input components was identified and fixed by ensuring  is converted to
  an empty string. Finally, a refinement pass addressed alert color consistency
  by introducing theme-based alert classes and increased the border opacity of
  section grouping boxes for better visual definition. The outcome is a
  significantly more cohesive, professional, and calming user interface tailored
  for a sleep health application.
